Description: Fragment of handle to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine buff-brown; small mica.
Curator's comments: Name Timaratos. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 31, 33. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0015.34.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1025)
